SIMPLE: circumspect
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Circumspect
<hw>Cir"cum*spect</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>circumspectus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>circumspicere</ets> to look
about one's self, to observe; <ets>circum + spicere</ets>,
<ets>specere</ets>, to look. See <er>Spy</er>.]</ety> <def>Attentive to
all the circumstances of a case or the probable consequences of an
action; cautious; prudent; wary.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Cautious</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Circumspection</ent>⟦br⟧
